@FORMAL (A → B)
@FORMAL (B → C)
@FORMAL (C → D)
@FORMAL A
@LOGIC D
@DERIVE Apply modus ponens to (A → B) and A to derive B, then apply hypothetical syllogism to (B → C) and (C → D) to derive (B → D), and finally apply modus ponens to (B → D) and B to derive D
@TAXONOMY ? OPEN
@STATE Derivation planned, awaiting execution by Agent B

@FORMAL (P → Q)
@FORMAL (Q → R)
@FORMAL ¬R
@LOGIC ¬P
@DERIVE [Modus Tollens, Hypothetical Syllogism]
@TAXONOMY ? OPEN
@STATE 
  Current Premises: [(P → Q), (Q → R), ¬R]
  Current Goal: ¬P
  Planned Rules: [Modus Tollens, Hypothetical Syllogism]

@FORMAL A ∧ B
@FORMAL C ∨ ¬B
@FORMAL C → D
@LOGIC D
@DERIVE [Modus Ponens, Disjunctive Syllogism, Simplification]
@TAXONOMY ? OPEN
@STATE 
  Current Premises: A ∧ B, C ∨ ¬B, C → D
  Current Goal: D
  Planned Rules: Modus Ponens, Disjunctive Syllogism, Simplification
  Status: Provisional Derivation Required

@FORMAL E ∨ F
@FORMAL E → G
@FORMAL F → H
@FORMAL ¬H
@LOGIC G
@DERIVE Disjunctive Syllogism, Modus Tollens, Modus Ponens
@TAXONOMY ? OPEN
@STATE E ∨ F, E → G, F → H, ¬H, Target: G, Planned Rules: Disjunctive Syllogism, Modus Tollens, Modus Ponens

@FORMAL (P ∨ Q → R)
@FORMAL P
@FORMAL (R → S)
@FORMAL T
@LOGIC S ∧ T
@DERIVE [Modus Ponens: (P ∨ Q → R) + P → R, Hypothetical Syllogism: (R → S) + R → S, Conjunction: S + T → S ∧ T]
@TAXONOMY ? OPEN 
@STATE Derivation initiated with premises and target proposition, awaiting further processing by Agent B.

